While you can get a quote online, there are several factors that affect your car insurance premiums.
 
State Farm offers multiple discounts that can lower your insurance rates, including:
 
State Farm is licensed in all 50 states and the District of Columbia. However, its rideshare insurance option is not available everywhere. Contact your local State Farm agent to see what coverage options are available in your area.
 
State Farm has more than 19,000 insurance agents nationwide. You can contact agents via phone, by email, or in person during normal business hours. If you need assistance outside business hours, State Farm’s customer service team is available via phone 24 hours a day, seven days a week.
 
State Farm's mobile app has won awards. In 2019 it was the Mobile Web Award winner for best insurance mobile app.﻿﻿ Available for both Android and iOS devices, you can use it to request emergency roadside assistance, file a claim, access your insurance ID cards, and contact your insurance agent.
 
State Farm has a strong reputation in the insurance industry. AM Best, a credit rating agency focused on the insurance industry, gave State Farm an A++ (Superior) Financial Strength rating, its highest. And, as noted above, in J.D. Power’s 2019 U.S. Auto Claims Satisfaction Study, State Farm was ranked fifth out of 23 national car insurers.
 
The National Association of Insurance Commissioners (NAIC) maintains a database of complaints about insurance companies. Each year the NAIC publishes companies’ complaint ratios, a number that reflects the amount of complaints a company received relative to its market share. Scores of 1.0 are considered average. Anything above 1.0 means the company received more complaints than is typical, while scores below 1.0 mean the reverse. In 2019 State Farm had a complaint ratio of 1.34, meaning it had a worse-than-average complaint ratio.﻿﻿
 For the past three years State Farm has had a slightly worse-than-average complaint ratio than the industry average. 
