You can file a claim via the mobile app, on the company’s website, or by calling your local State Farm agent. If you would like to report a claim over the phone after normal business hours, you can call 800-732-5246.
 
To report a claim, you will be asked to provide: 
 
After you report your claim, State Farm will review the details. It will contact you if it needs additional information and to notify you about next steps. An agent will let you know about your estimate and repair options.
 
You can cancel your State Farm policy without paying a cancellation fee. You can cancel your policy over the phone, in person, or through the mail. You can contact your local agent or call 800-782-8332. When you’re ready to cancel, be prepared to provide your policy number, name, and date of birth.
 
You can get a car insurance quote from State Farm online. To do so, you’ll need to enter the following information about your car and yourself:
 
State Farm will use this information to generate your quote, which you can customize.
 
State Farm is the largest car insurance company in the country, and it offers multiple coverage options and discounts. However, it’s not the best insurance company for everyone. Depending on your location, driving history, and vehicle, State Farm may be more expensive than your other options. Before selecting an insurer, it’s a good idea to compare quotes from multiple companies.
 For drivers looking for a robust insurance company with multiple coverage options, State Farm is hard to beat. Not only does it offer a wide range of auto insurance coverages and discounts; you can also combine your policy with homeowners or renter’s insurance, life insurance, and even pet insurance. State Farm allows you to connect with local agents for personalized assistance, and it has customer service representatives available 24/7 if you need to file a claim or have questions about your policy. It’s an excellent choice for car insurance for many drivers. 
